text: Sivry-Rance is a municipality found in the Belgian province of Hainaut. Annie Debruxelles is a mayor. In 2018, its population was 4,833. It is found at 50° 10 North, 04° 10 East. The area is 72.97 km2. It has 5 sub-municipalities: Grandrieu, Montbliart, Rance, Sautin, and Sivry. ==References== Category:Municipalities of Hainaut
title: Sivry-Rance
